==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Freak
<hw>Freak</hw> <pr>(fr⟦emac⟧k)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Freaked</conjf> <pr>(fr⟦emac⟧kt)</pr>; <pos>p. pr.
& vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Freaking</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Akin to OE.
<ets>frakin</ets>, <ets>freken</ets>, freckle, Icel. <ets>freknur</ets>,
pl., Sw. <ets>fr⟦aum⟧kne</ets>, Dan. <ets>fregne</ets>, Gr.
<grk>perkno`s</grk> dark-colored, Skr. <ets>p⟦rsdot⟧⟦cced⟧ni</ets>
variegated. Cf. <er>Freckle</er>, <er>Freck</er>.]</ety> <def>To
variegate; to checker; to streak.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Freaked</qex> with many a mingled hue.</q>
<rj><qau>Thomson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Freak</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Freak
<hw>Freak</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. from OE. <ets>frek</ets> bold,
AS. <ets>frec</ets> bold, greedly; akin to OHG. <ets>freh</ets> greedly,
G. <ets>frech</ets> insolent, Icel. <ets>frekr</ets> greedy, Goth.
<ets>fa⟦iacute⟧hufriks</ets> avaricious.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
sudden causeless change or turn of the mind; a whim of fancy; a
capricious prank; a vagary or caprice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She is restless and peevish, and sometimes in a <qex>freak</qex>
will instantly change her habitation.</q>
<rj><qau>Spectator.</qau></rj></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a rare and unpredictable event; <as>as, the July
snowstorm was a <ex>freak</ex> of nature</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>an habitual drug user, especially one who uses
psychedelic drugs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>an animal or person with a visible congenital
abnormality; -- applied especially to those who appear in a circus
sideshow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Whim; caprice; folly; sport. See
<er>Whim</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Freak</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Freak
<hw>Freak</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>to react with
irrationality or extreme emotion; to lose one's composure; -- often used
in the phrase <col><b>freak out</b></col>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>to become irrational or to experience hallucinations
under the influence of drugs; -- often used in the phrase <col><b>freak
out</b></col>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Freak</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Freak
<hw>Freak</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>to cause (a person)
react with great distress or extreme emotion; -- often used in the
phrase <col><b>freak out</b></col>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Freaking</ent>⟦br⟧
